Tomb C.2
Date: Dec. 21
Turba 180 x 60
Body disturbed, remains of wood coffin.

Date: Dec. 21
Turba 220 x 70
Body in wood coffin, extended on back, head N-W.
[drawing]

Tomb: C6
Date: Dec. 21-22
Shaft with superstructure as shown in plan.
Two ch. to N & two to S.
Upper N.: Wooden kohl stick; Ivory kohl stick (?)
Upper S.: Broken Canopic jar lid head, limestone
Lower N.: Plaster eye from small mask.
Lower S.: Three vases drawn, one of them [...] top; Ushabti head; Sealing in mud of later Dyn scarab; Head rest of wood
Plan

Tomb C7
Date: Dec. 23
Shaft.
N. ch.
7 bl. gl. & 2 white discoid beads
S.

Tomb C9.
Date: Dec. 24
Shaft.
Ch. to S.
Part of wooden figure
Half an ivory bracelet
Piece of stucco sarcophagus
Small dish in upper radîm
One bl. gl. bead

Tomb: C11
Date: Dec 24th
[drawing]
Burial of child in wood coffin. Covered with large stones, & big boulder on top. Stones packed in later. Side of coffin on E. side of turba.

Tomb: C.12
Date: Dec. 24th
Shaft.
In shaft pieces of black incised pot. & of a plain one.
Pottery bowl.

Tomb: C.13
Date: Dec. 25
Turba on the west side of shaft 14, clearly later than it.
Body of old man on back, head to right, extended, legs slightly bent by fall of coffin lid. Each limb wrapped in several thick [...] of coarse linen.
On head a cartonnage head with v. small face, stucco v. thick
Under face an ochre bowl with red rim.
Head local N.

Tomb: C.21
Date: Dec. 24th
Shaft.
N. ch.
Linen, with fringe
& inscribed band
Glass paste beads, [drawing] white, lemon yellow, brick red, green, blue, also [drawing] 
Late forms [drawings]
Pieces of Ushabtis of light blue glaze, prob. 22nd.

Tomb: C51
Date: Dec 21-2
Dynasty xii-xvii
Rect. shaft NW& SE 305 x 120
[drawing]
South chamber. Roof fallen in,  & connected with 52 S2. Plundered, but not completely.
1 ivory wand uninscribed (broken) 1/2 another (hand [...]) hand of a third. Broken alabaster vase [drawing] (drawn). Fragts. of painted wood coffin. Small carnelian scarab. Fragts. of gold leaf. Flat round white beads. Flat round gold beads. 3 drop-shaped crystal? glazed beads.

Tomb: C52
Date: Dec. 21-2
Dynasty: xii-xviii
Dimensions 285 x 100 x 4.30 (top of N.2) bottom of N1 at 315.
Rect. shaft. NW. & SE. Two chambers to N & two to S. 
[drawing]
Fragts. of painted wooden coffin, ivory wand from shaft.
In S.2. 3 pottery canopic jars without heads or inscriptions; 2 bronze earrings. Chamber much broken in & plundered.
N.2. Too broken for safe working. Two fragts. of decayed wooden coffin.
N.1. 1/2 bricked up. 3 bodies not in position.

Fragts. of decayed wood coffin painted. Alabaster kohl pot. Copper tweezers. Series of pottery (drawn).
S.1
Roof broken in & plundered. 3 bodies.
Fragts. of alabaster vase, arm of ivory wand (broken). Fragts. of ivory [...] inlay, small black stone, kohl-pot in white stone base (lid missing). Amethyst scarab (broken). Small carnelian scarab (complete). Alabaster amulet [drawing] (complete). Fragts. of red woolly substance. Flat white, round metal, blue glaze bead.

Tomb: C53
Date: Dec. 21-2
Rect. shaft. NW & S.E. Chamber
N & S. Both empty.

Tomb: C54
Date: Dec 24th
Rect. shaft NW. & S.E. Thoroughly plundered.
N.2 Pieces of oval & oblong bl. gl. inlay. Fragts. of painted wood coffin. [drawing]. Worked flint flake. Small pot [drawing].
N.1. Completley empty.

Tomb: C56
Date: Dec 24th
Rect. shaft. NW. 1 SE. out of shaft
unbaked mud dish in fragts. with thin painted white lines.
Out of S. Chamber incised black-topped "Pan" pot in fragts.
North chamber completely empty?

Tomb: C62
Date: Dec. 23
Broad shaft, with fine bricking. At the bottom bricked on 3 sides to hold back the gebel.
Chamber of large size but much broken, to S. for finds.
Small piece of gold foil in shaft.

Tomb: C63
Date: Dec. 21-2
Rect. shaft 270 x 100 x 350
52° W. of N.
two ch. at bottom, one to N, one to S.
South ch. 220 x 100 x 95. one ochre bowl, few white discoid beads.
North ch. 215 x 100 x 95. empty
In the shaft several vases.
Sectn.

Tomb: C64.
Date: Dec. 23
Shaft. In the shaft near bottom many white discoid beads, dark blue barrel-shaped, & a few light blue glaze
N. Ch. a Pan-pot & a bowl of pottery & part of a 'flint-stand'
S. ch. Thoroughly plundered. Fragts. of painted wood coffin belonging to [hieroglyphs].

Tomb: C65
Date: Dec. 23
Shaft.
Ch. to N & S.

Tomb: C66
Date: Dec. 24-5
Shaft. ch. to S. only.
2 sarcophagi with blue hieroglyphs badly disturbed
vases drawn, white spated etc.
One of the sarcoph. has name of owner filled in in hieratic.

Tomb: C71
Date: Dec. 21st
A low circular structure as planned [drawing]
both of wall 16. ht. of wall above dalslsa 25
A dalslsa surrounded by low wall
Broken vase on dalslsa as shown.

Tomb: C72
Date: Dec. 22
Turba north of 71.
Body extended, a little on left side in wood coffin head N. 22° W.
No finds.

Tomb: C73
Date: Dec. 22
Round structure originally surrounded by 4 others.
See plan.
Plan

Tomb: C74
Dec 23
Dynasty: ?
Much disturbed body. Extended burial in wood coffin. NW & S.E.
[drawing]
Two bl. gl. beads. [drawing]

Date: Dec. 23
Turba
Child extended, head N.
[drawings]
2 beads of stone
The vases stood 30 cm. above coffin & may not belong to burial
B might belong to 76.
[drawings]

Tomb: C76
Date: Dec 23rd.
Dynasty: xii-xviii
Body (female) lying on back right leg slightly bent under left. Lying S.W.  N.E. Head to right. On right upper arm 2 strings of beads, one flat white, one small round black; ditto on r. forearm. On finger, ring of minute blue lge beads.
Left upper arm same as right. Nothing on forearm. Ring on finger of minute black glaze beads. Round neck 3 necklaces a) Flat white beads, with alabaster pendant b) Larger dark & light blue glaze beads
[drawing]

threaded alternately. c) Smaller black blue glaze beads threaded in proportion of about 8 black to one blue. pendant [drawing] of blue glaze crystal (?) brokeb.
At each ear six small blue glaze flat beads.

Tomb: C77
Date: Dec. 23
Turba distubed, head N
A few white discoid beads.

Tomb: C78
Date: Dec. 24
Body in wood coffin, head N, much disturbed.
This lay 30 cm. from top of a broad shaft which ran blind below it.

Tomb: C79
Date: Dec. 24
Turba under the south of shaft walls 81 & 82.
body extended on l. side head to E.
[drawing]

Tomb: C.81
Date: Dec. 28-30
Dynasty: =X.40. 1911.
A large hôsh with mastaba & shaft & ramp leading down to "garden" (No. 73), planned last year.
Near it a series of mastabas (planned) some with turbas, some with shafts are plan.
[drawing]
Both empty.
Note mastaba 82 was in place before the ramp was built, for its white plaster runs all round, while the ramp is not plastered at this point 
see over

[plan]
Note that ramp was added to [...] after the latter was plastered white.

Tomb: C84
Date: Dec. 28
Shaft near 81. See plan
Ch. to S. badly distubed.
In shaft Pieces of small stucco face & ears
Piece of green paste pot (no glaze)
Fine semi transparent white pebble
White discoid shell beads & 1 bl. gl. discoid
two objs of mud
[drawings]
Over

[drawing] green & blue glaze bead.
piece of white spot red ware.

Date: Dec. 25
Shaft.
2 lower ch. to N & S. fall of rock prevented working
1 upper to S. Piece of red ware with black rim; Piece of small stucco face; Wood kohl stick; Beads (1) White discoid (2) [drawing] glaze, light & dark blue similar to the smaller beads of 76.

N 37 W.

Round structure originally surrounded by 4 others, See plan.

Much disturbed body. Extended burial in wood coffin. NW & SE.

Turba.
Child extended, head N.
The vases stood 30 cm. above coffin & may not belong to burial. B might belong to 76.

Tomb: C 76:
Body (female symbol) on back right leg slightly bent under left. Lying SW to NE. Head to right. On right upper arm 2 strings of beads, one flat white, one small round black; ditto on R forearm. On finger, ring of minute blue glaze beads. Left upper arm same as right. Nothing on forearm. Ring on finger of minute blue glaze beads. Round neck 3 necklaces: 
a) Flat white beads, with alabaster pendant.
b) Larger dark-blue & light blue glaze beads.

Threaded alternately.
c) Small black & blue glaze beads threaded in proportion of about 8 black to one blue. Pendant of blue glaze crystal?, broken.
At each ear six small blue glaze flat beads.

Tomb: C 77:
Turba disturbed, head N.
A few white discoid beads.

Tomb: C 78:
Body in wood coffin, head N, much disturbed.

Tomb: C 79:
Turba under the south of shaft walls 81 & 82.

Tomb: C 81:
A large kush with mastaba & shaft & ramp leading down to "garden" (No. 73), planned last year.
Near it a series of mastabas (pl[...]) some with turbas, some with shafts are [...].
Note mastaba 82 was in place before the ramp was built, for its white plaster was all round, while the ramp is not plastered at this point. See over -

White plaster of mastaba.
Dirt & sand
Later white plaster, ie. that of ramp.
Note that ramp was added to kush after the latter was plastered white.

body disturbed.

OVER
